Boston Cream Pie
  --America's Test Kitchen

Pastry cream
6 yolks
pinch of salt
1/2 c sugar
1/4 c ap flour
2 c half and half
4 tbsp unsalted butter
1 1/2 tsp vanilla

Whisk yolks, salt, and sugar until nice and smooth. Add flour and whisk until combined. Bring half and half to a simmer, take 1/2 c and use to temper the egg mixture. Pour egg mixture back into pot and whisk until thick over medium heat, turn heat down to medium low for 8 min, then turn heat up to medium and cook a minute more, whisking whole time. Take off heat add butter and vanilla. Pour into a bowl using a fine mesh strainer. Take a piece of parchment and spray with oil, press down into top of cream and place in refriegerator for at least 2hrs, up to 24 hrs.

Cake
3/4 c whole milk
6 tbsp unsalted butter
1 1/2 tsp vanilla
1 1/2 c ap flour
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
3/4 tsp salt
3 eggs
1 1/2 c sugar


PReheat oven to 325F. Prep 2x9" cake pans, grease and flour, line bottom with parchment and grease that. Heat milk and butter over low heat; add vanilla and cover off heat. Combine flour, salt, and baking powder in a bowl, set aside. Add eggs and sugar to bowl of a stand mixer with whisk attachment and whisk on high until light and fluffy, ~5 min. Mix in hot milk mixture. Whisk in dry ingredients until combined. Pour into cake pans. Bake for 20-22 min until tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool before removing from pans, flip out onto wire rack.

Glaze
4 oz bittersweet chocolate, chopped finely
2 tbsp light corn syrup
1/2 c heavy cream

Heat cream over medium heat, add corn syrup and bring to simmer. Take off heat, add chocolate and whisk until melted, ~30 sec. Let stand for 5 min.


Assemble
Place on layer of cake, spread layer of cream, top with cake, put in refrigerator for a little bit. Glaze with chocolate. Put back into refrigerator for at least 3 hrs to set up. Can make it a day in advance.
